description:
&lt;p&gt;Torbay and South Devon Healthcare is a Foundation Trust which provides healthcare services for a population of over 300,000. The Laboratory Medicine Directorate provides a comprehensive Pathology service for the Acute Trust, associated NHS organisations and GPs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Central Pathology Reception provides a vital role for the Laboratory Medicine directorate in the pre-analytical processing and data entry of over 3000 blood samples a day for the Biochemistry and Haematology Laboratories and approximately 600 samples for Microbiology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The laboratory uses the Laboratory Information System Winpath 5.32 . Electronic requesting is carried out via Cyberlab but some manual data entry is still carried out.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A position is now available in this busy Department. You will be expected to work20 Hours per week (Core hours are 09:00 - 5.30pm Monday – Friday (with expectation to work on some days until 6pm on a rotational basis. In addition to this, you will be required to work Saturdays and Bank Holidays).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to work well as part as a team and have excellent communication skills and telephone manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Alison Miles (Reception Supervisor) on 01803 655207 or Patrick Lee 01803 655206.&lt;/p&gt;
